Mountain Stance					KEY:Mountain Stance ~ Mountain Druid		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ArchetypeDruid.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary.DruidVenomImmunity																																																																									DESC:At 9th level, a mountain druid gains immunity to petrification and receives a +4 bonus on saving throws or to CMD to resist any attempt to push, pull, bull rush, or drag her, or to resist any other effect that would physically move her from her position (e.g., repel wood, reverse gravity, or being blown away by high winds). This does not protect her against being tripped, grappled, or overrun. This ability replaces venom immunity.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.100
Mountain Stone					KEY:Mountain Stone ~ Mountain Druid			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ArchetypeDruid.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary.DruidThousandFaces																																																																									DESC:At 13th level, a mountain druid can transform her body into a weathered stone outcrop and back at will. This effect functions as statue. This ability replaces a thousand faces.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.100

# Plains Druid
Plains Traveler					KEY:Plains Traveler ~ Plains Druid			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ArchetypeDruid.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary.DruidWoodlandStride																																																																									DESC:At 2nd level, a plains druid gains a bonus on initiative checks and Knowledge (geography), Perception, Stealth, and Survival checks equal to 1/2 her druid level in plains terrain, and she cannot be tracked in such an environment. This ability replaces woodland stride.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.100
Run Like the Wind					KEY:Run Like the Wind ~ Plains Druid		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ArchetypeDruid.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary.DruidTracklessStep																																																																									DESC:At 3rd level, a plains druid gains +10 feet to her land speed when wearing light or no armor and carrying a light load, and once per hour, she may run or charge at double the normal speed for 1 round. If riding her animal companion, it gains this ability instead. This ability replaces trackless step.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.100
Savanna Ambush					KEY:Savanna Ambush ~ Plains Druid			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ArchetypeDruid.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary.DruidResistNaturesLure																																																																									DESC:At 4th level, a plains druid gains concealment whenever she is prone in natural surroundings, and can make Stealth checks at no penalty when prone and not moving or at -5 when crawling. A plains druid can stand up from prone as an immediate action during a surprise round. This ability replaces resist nature's lure.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.100
Wild Shape						KEY:Wild Shape ~ Plains Druid				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ArchetypeDruid.SpecialQuality.Supernatural.DruidWildShape																																																																										DESC:A plains druid gains this ability at 6th level, except that her effective druid level for the ability is equal to her druid level - 2.																																																																																																																																												ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Druid Wild Shape|Druid Wild Shape Progression|Druid Wild Shape Times																																																BONUS:VAR|DruidWildShape|-2																																																																				SOURCEPAGE:p.100
Canny Charger					KEY:Canny Charger ~ Plains Druid			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ArchetypeDruid.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary.DruidVenomImmunity																																																																									DESC:At 9th level, a plains druid can charge through allies' squares without difficulty (whether mounted or afoot) and can turn up to 90 degrees once during a charge, provided the last 10 feet toward the target are in a straight line. She also gains a +4 dodge bonus to AC against enemy charge attacks and a +4 bonus to damage with a readied action against a charging foe. This ability replaces venom immunity.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.100
Evasion						KEY:Evasion ~ Plains Druid				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ArchetypeDruid.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary.DruidThousandFaces																																																																									DESC:At 13th level, a plains druid gains evasion when wearing light or no armor and carrying a light load. This functions as the rogue ability of the same name. This ability replaces a thousand faces.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																											SOURCEPAGE:p.100

