Guileful Polyglot			KEY:Guileful Polyglot Language Selection	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:GuilefulPolygotLang.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																															DESC:A rogue with this talent who has at least one rank in Linguistics gains four additional languages. A rogue with this talent who does not have any ranks in Linguistics gains two additional languages. If the rogue later gains ranks in Linguistics, she gains two additional languages, to a total of four additional languages above those granted by the Linguistics skill itself. &nl;Languages selected - %1|%LIST																														MULT:YES	CHOOSE:LANG|!PC,QUALIFIED						AUTO:LANG|%LIST																																																				SOURCEPAGE:p.130


# Block: Advanced Rogue Talents:
Another Day				KEY:Another Day ~ Rogue Talent		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:RogueTalent.Extraordinary.SpecialQuality																				PREVARGTEQ:RogueTalentLVL,10								DESC:Once per day, when the rogue would be reduced to 0 or fewer hit points by a melee attack, she can take a 5-foot step as an immediate action. If the movement takes her out of the reach of the attack, she takes no damage from the attack. The rogue is staggered for 1 round on her next turn.																																																																																																																				SOURCEPAGE:p.131
Deadly Cocktail			KEY:Deadly Cocktail ~ Rogue Talent		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:RogueTalent.Extraordinary.SpecialQuality																				PREVARGTEQ:RogueTalentLVL,10								DESC:A rogue with this talent can apply two doses of poison to a weapon at once. These can be separate poisons, in which case they both affect the target individually, or two doses of the same toxin, in which case the poisons' frequency is extended by 50%% and the save DC increases by +2. This talent is an exception to the rule that injury poisons can only be delivered one dose at a time.																																																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.131
Deadly Sneak**			KEY:Deadly Sneak ~ Rogue Talent		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:RogueTalent.Extraordinary.SpecialAttack.AttackOption				PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Powerful Sneak ~ Rogue Talent			PREVARGTEQ:RogueTalentLVL,10								DESC:Whenever a rogue with this talent uses the powerful sneak rogue talent, she treats all 1s and 2s on the sneak attack damage dice as 3s. A rogue must have the powerful sneak rogue talent before choosing this talent.																																																																																																																																SOURCEPAGE:p.131
Entanglement of Blades**	KEY:Entanglement of Blades ~ Rogue Talent	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:RogueTalent.Extraordinary.SpecialAttack.AttackOption																		PREVARGTEQ:RogueTalentLVL,10								DESC:When a rogue with this talent hits a creature with a melee attack that deals sneak attack damage, the target cannot take a 5-foot step until the beginning of the rogue's next turn.																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.131
Fast Tumble				KEY:Fast Tumble ~ Rogue Talent		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:RogueTalent.Extraordinary.SpecialQuality																				PREVARGTEQ:RogueTalentLVL,10								DESC:When a rogue with this talent uses Acrobatics to move at full speed through a threatened square without provoking an attack of opportunity, the DC of the Acrobatics check does not increase by 10.																																																																																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.131
Frugal Trapsmith			KEY:Frugal Trapsmith ~ Rogue Talent		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:RogueTalent.Extraordinary.SpecialQuality																				PREVARGTEQ:RogueTalentLVL,10								DESC:When a rogue with this talent constructs a mechanical trap, she only pays 75%% of the normal cost.																																																																																																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.132
Hunter's Surprise			KEY:Hunter's Surprise ~ Rogue Talent	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:RogueTalent.Extraordinary.SpecialAttack.AttackOption																		PREVARGTEQ:RogueTalentLVL,10								DESC:Once per day, a rogue with this talent can designate a single enemy she is adjacent to as her prey. Until the end of her next turn, she can add her sneak attack damage to all attacks made against her prey, even if she is not flanking it or it is not flat-footed.																																																																																																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.132
Knock-Out Blow			KEY:Knock-Out Blow ~ Rogue Talent		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:RogueTalent.Extraordinary.SpecialAttack.AttackOption																		PREVARGTEQ:RogueTalentLVL,10								DESC:Once per day, the rogue can forgo her sneak attack damage to attempt to knock out an opponent. She must declare the use of knock-out blow before she makes the attack. If the attack hits, it does normal damage, but instead of dealing sneak attack damage (and instead of any effect that triggers when the rogue deals sneak attack damage), the target falls unconscious for 1d4 rounds. A successful Fortitude save reduces this effect to staggered for 1 round. The DC is %1 [save is equal to 10 + 1/2 the rogue's level + the rogue's Intelligence modifier].|10+(RogueTalentLVL/2)+INT																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.132
Master of Disguise		KEY:Master of Disguise ~ Rogue Talent	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:RogueTalent.Extraordinary.SpecialQuality																				PREVARGTEQ:RogueTalentLVL,10								DESC:Once per day, a rogue with this talent gains a +10 bonus on a single Disguise check.																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.132
Redirect Attack			KEY:Redirect Attack ~ Rogue Talent		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:RogueTalent.Extraordinary.SpecialQuality																				PREVARGTEQ:RogueTalentLVL,10								DESC:Once per day, when a rogue with this talent is hit with a melee attack, she can redirect the attack to strike at an adjacent creature with a free action. The creature targeted must be within melee reach of the attack that hit the rogue, and the creature that made the attack against the rogue must make a new attack roll against the new target.																																																																																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.132
Stealthy Sniper			KEY:Stealthy Sniper ~ Rogue Talent		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:RogueTalent.Extraordinary.SpecialQuality																				PREVARGTEQ:RogueTalentLVL,10								DESC:When a rogue with this talent uses the Stealth skill to snipe, she only suffers a -10 penalty on the Stealth check, instead of -20.																																																																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.132
Thoughtful Reexamining		KEY:Thoughtful Reexamining ~ Rogue Talent	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:RogueTalent.Extraordinary.SpecialQuality																				PREVARGTEQ:RogueTalentLVL,10								DESC:Once per day, a rogue with this talent can reroll a Knowledge, Sense Motive, or Perception skill check to try to gain new or better information from the roll. This reroll can be made any time during the same day as the original check.																																																																																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.132

